<h1 id="facilitation">Facilitation</h1>
There are two ways to use this app: The first way is to assign a facilitator to oversee the process. This is the traditional way to conduct Convergent Facilitation, and gives one person the role of guiding the group towards a satisfactory outcome. The second way is to conduct the convergent facilitation process without a facilitator. This can be useful for quick decisions, for groups that do not have a trained facilitator, or for groups that wish to distribute power as much as possible.
<h2>Facilitator mode</h2>
<p>If you select "facilitator mode" when creating a new collaboration, you will be assigned the facilitator for that decision. As facilitator, you must approve new criteria before they are listed as active. To view unapproved criteria, click <span class="click">All</span> under the criteria section.</p>
